Until no one ever fell off the earth did we know that that wasn't true either. It's ignorant of you to say that we now know what is true and not true just because we are "advanced". Everything should be questioned because, just as science shows us, nothing it absolute.

bigtime979- I normally never do this, reply to people's ranting. But i had to this time.

Is nothing absolute?, 
maybe it depends on the person,
If nothing is absolute, then how the fucking hell do you "know" that "we found out" that the sun revolves around the earth, or the world isn't flat?

Who is 'we'?

Were you on this great expedition to the stars?

Or did your neighbor tell you it was true?

Have you been to space? Have you seen it for yourself? 
You said , "Everything should be questioned" So why is it that you don't question "scientific facts" that have been dictated to you all your life? (by "your girlfriend")

You tell us to have an open mind but then tell us what the truth "really is".

I'm not saying there is any truth to anything in this movie, BECAUSE I have an open mind.

Having an open mind doesn't mean doubting everything you've ever known and believing in the most fantastical ideas without a doubt.
To have an open mind means to be open to absolutely every side. And be completely non-bias towards one side or the other. And you NEED to have a TRUE open mind when taking in stuff about aliens and the bible and every other alter realistic crazy subject. 
My advice:
DON"T BELIEVE IT WITHOUT THINKING, WITHOUT DOUBTING. TREAT IT THE SAME WAY YOU DO WITH THE STUFF YOU'VE BEEN TOLD ALL YOUR LIFE. 
THE TRUTH IS OUT THERE, but don't be so fuckin naive that you think you've found it..

a truly open mind - its a recipe for sanity.
